Planar exploration:

I'm going to need to set some DCs for various things they could try to do.

Using one of the presets is going to be a high DC Arcana check the first few
times, then she'll get the hang of it. (Smol's the only one of the two who can
read the Netherese.) If she does decide to point it at one of the presets, the
location within the plane will be somewhere far from busy places, just like
the part of the hells the portal is currently pointed at... Am I correct in
thinking time passes at a different speed in Faerie than in the prime
material? Is it faster or slower or just different or DM's choice?

I think successfully targeting a known plane that isn't already a preset is
something that would take many months. In however long the Netherese had this
thing running they only found found four locations they wanted to save in the
presets, and three of them are (as I understand it) relatively easy to get to
other ways.

Targeting an unknown plane takes less time (because there are so many of
them), but finding one that is in any way useful would still take many weeks.
Finding an unknown plane with a specific trait (like "futuristic") would take
longer than finding a known plane.

Changing the location within a plane that they already have a connection to is
something they can learn in a day and takes a few minutes once they learn it.

If they focus entirely on making the portal point somewhere besides the
presets, they'll have to set up a system for keeping themselves fed and such
while they work at the machine, and if they do all that in session 8, the
cliffhanger will be them finding a new plane.

As for the unknown presets... I don't remember what I said about that either.
I'll ask the kids about that too.

